Solution:
Completing the square in $x$ and $y$, we get
\[(x - 5)^2 - 25 + (y + 3)^2 - 9 = 0.\]This simplifies to $(x - 5)^2 + (y + 3)^2 = 34.$

Thus, $x - 5$ and $y + 3$ lie on a circle centered at $(5,-3)$ with radius $\sqrt{34}.$  Therefore, $x + y = \boxed{2}.$

[asy]
unitsize(0.5 cm);

pair[] O;
real[] r;
pair A, B, C, D;

O[1] = (5,-3);
r[1] = sqrt(34);
A = (5,0);
B = (0,-3);
C = (5 - r[1],0);
D = (0,-3 - r[1]);

draw(Circle(O[1],r[1]));
draw((-2,0)--(8,0));
draw((0,-6)--(0,4));
draw(A--(C + r[1]*dir(225)));
draw(B--(D + r[1]*dir(-45)));

label("$\sqrt{34}$", (O[1] + C)/2, SE);

dot("$A$", A, N);
dot("$B$", B, W);
dot("$O$", O[1], S);
dot("$C$", C, SW);
dot("$D$", D, NE);
[/asy]

